$ PowerShell: determine version with get-host

The → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/host/get[`get-host` cmdLet] allows to determine the current version of → Windows/PowerShell:
code {
PS C:\> (get-host).version

Major  Minor  Build  Revision
-----  -----  -----  --------
5      1      17763  134
code }

sa:
  → Windows/PowerShell/language/variable/automatic/PsVersionTable#psVersion-powerShell-version[Determine PowerShell version with `$psVersionTable`].
